    "body": "## Problem\r\nWhen using `vim.list.unique` or `vim.list.bisect`, if the `key` function is complex, it can degrade performance, because it is invoked on every comparison\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nThe `key` interface convention is designed specifically to address this issue; performance can be improved by memoizing its results.\r\n\r\nAlso added the shorthand use of the field name string as the key.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-05T21:04:12Z",
    "comment_data": [
