        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This seems a bit of a strange change to me given that it increases the memory consumption even for cases where the key function is cheap. It is quite common for methods like this to be used with a simple property accessor/key lookup, so caching the result into another table is pretty much wasted.\r\n\r\nWhy not leave it up to users to compose things with a `memoize` / `once` function? ",
